than what they're saying,

500
00:28:08,395 --> 00:28:10,231
then what are we supposed to do?

501
00:28:10,314 --> 00:28:13,359
Are we supposed to go along
with their act?

502
00:28:13,442 --> 00:28:15,361
-That's right.
-Yes, that's true.

503
00:28:15,444 --> 00:28:17,654
I was watching so intently.

504
00:28:17,738 --> 00:28:20,449
We're really in a panic right now.

505
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:23,535
How can you act lovey-dovey
with the guy you like

506
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:25,454
without bringing your TV image down?

507
00:28:25,537 --> 00:28:26,913
So you act lovey-dovey
when the camera's off.

508
00:28:26,997 --> 00:28:30,501
And in front of the camera,
you act the best image of yourself.

509
00:28:30,584 --> 00:28:32,294
That's what these two realized.

510
00:28:32,378 --> 00:28:33,462
-That's what it is.
-Yes.

511
00:28:33,545 --> 00:28:37,215
Then what was all that about going to
amusement parks only with a boyfriend?

512
00:28:37,299 --> 00:28:42,095
So she was acting the part
of an innocent, shy girl on TV.

513
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:48,894
Shock.

514
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:52,898
It's the gap of what they're doing
and what they're trying to show on TV.

515
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:54,483
That gap is sneaky.

516
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:56,860
"So you don't mind if he held your hand?"

517
00:28:56,943 --> 00:28:58,654
"No, I want to save that."

518
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:02,073
I was just remembering
how she said that so adamantly.

519
00:29:02,157 --> 00:29:03,992
They don't have my support anymore.

520
00:29:07,579 --> 00:29:08,955
I can't believe them anymore!

521
00:29:09,039 --> 00:29:11,500
-This is crazy.
-It is crazy.

522
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:12,709
I can't believe them.

523
00:29:12,793 --> 00:29:17,213
This is the biggest shocker
since <i>Terrace House</i> started.

524
00:29:17,298 --> 00:29:20,008
-It's a major incident.
-Very major.

525
00:29:20,091 --> 00:29:23,136
Wow, this is entertainment!

526
00:29:23,219 --> 00:29:25,431
What's great is there's still video left.

527
00:29:25,514 --> 00:29:26,848
And that thanks to this incident,

528
00:29:26,932 --> 00:29:28,725
we've forgotten things
are going well for Arman.

529
00:29:29,935 --> 00:29:32,771
-That's right! It looked good for Arman.
-We're sorry!

530
00:29:32,854 --> 00:29:35,732
Except when the train
passed by the café.

531
00:29:35,816 --> 00:29:37,693
He should've said, "Because I like you."

532
00:29:37,776 --> 00:29:39,445
Yeah, the whole
"it's been more fun recently."

533
00:29:39,528 --> 00:29:42,989
"Why?"
"Because you're here."

534
00:29:44,700 --> 00:29:46,117
"What did you say?"

535
00:29:46,201 --> 00:29:47,202
"Oh, nothing."

536
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:49,663
He had a chance for that kind of scene!

537
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:52,291
Instead he said, "There's a train."

538
00:29:52,999 --> 00:29:54,876
-Very serious.
-Very serious.

539
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,796
It was his chance
for an unforgettable scene!

540
00:29:57,879 --> 00:29:59,923
Is it a good thing then?
That she's comfortable with him?

541
00:30:00,006 --> 00:30:02,426
Should guys take that as a chance
if a girl says that to them?

542
00:30:02,509 --> 00:30:05,304
It could go either way.

543
00:30:05,387 --> 00:30:07,639
It could mean she doesn't see him
as a man.

544
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:09,891
I won't go so far as to say that,

545
00:30:09,975 --> 00:30:13,269
but often it's like,
"We're not like that."

546
00:30:13,354 --> 00:30:16,482
Masako is vulnerable right now,
but in any case...

547
00:30:16,565 --> 00:30:18,775
-putting that aside.
-Rather...

548
00:30:18,859 --> 00:30:20,902
-We should listen to what they say.
-That's true.

549
00:30:20,986 --> 00:30:23,614
I'm sure Prosecutor Byrnes
will be questioning them.

550
00:30:23,697 --> 00:30:25,366
-Prosecutor Byrnes?
-Yes, Prosecutor Byrnes.

551
00:30:25,449 --> 00:30:27,534
-Prosecutor Byrnes.
-No, no...

552
00:30:27,618 --> 00:30:29,620
{\an8}It's not Kenji Moriwaki.

553
00:30:29,703 --> 00:30:31,788
{\an8}KENJI MORIWAKI

554
00:30:31,872 --> 00:30:34,290
He'll get to the bottom of things.

555
00:30:34,375 --> 00:30:37,210
-We have to hear their thoughts.
-I can't believe them.

556
00:30:37,794 --> 00:30:40,714
Going to Kagoshima for a shoot.
-Martha

557
00:30:41,757 --> 00:30:46,011
{\an8}I'm kind of reaching my limit.

558
00:30:47,929 --> 00:30:51,475
When he came back to our room
after the fireworks,

559
00:30:51,558 --> 00:30:53,852
he said he can't see her as a woman.

560
00:30:53,935 --> 00:30:56,021
That he can't hold hands with her
or kiss her.

561
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:58,023
-That's what he said.
-He did.

562
00:30:58,106 --> 00:31:01,317
-He's totally doing all that.
-Yeah, all of it.

563
00:31:01,402 --> 00:31:02,736
Yeah.

564
00:31:02,819 --> 00:31:06,365
Knowing all this,

565
00:31:06,448 --> 00:31:09,493
I can't really give advice
to Hayato anymore.

566
00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:12,663
You mean how even though things
are progressing between them,

567
00:31:12,746 --> 00:31:15,123
we have to pretend we don't know.

568
00:31:15,206 --> 00:31:16,375
Yeah.

569
00:31:16,458 --> 00:31:19,878
Making conversation
even though we know...

570
00:31:19,961 --> 00:31:22,338
-It's not real.
-Yeah.

571
00:31:22,423 --> 00:31:26,342
We should be clear about that.

572
00:31:26,427 --> 00:31:27,511
It's just not fair.

573
00:31:31,264 --> 00:31:32,683
-Welcome back.
-I'm back.

574
00:31:32,766 --> 00:31:34,309
-Welcome back.
-I'm back.

575
00:31:34,393 --> 00:31:35,602
Hey, Hayato.

576
00:31:36,562 --> 00:31:37,646
I'm back.

577
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,355
Let's have a drink.

578
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:41,107
Sure.

579
00:31:41,191 --> 00:31:42,192
I'm exhausted.

580
00:31:42,275 --> 00:31:43,902
-Should I go get her?
-You don't seem tired.

581
00:31:50,784 --> 00:31:52,077
It's been a while.

582
00:31:53,161 --> 00:31:55,038
-What?
-Us drinking together.

583
00:31:58,249 --> 00:31:59,668
It hasn't been that long.

584
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:01,211
-No way.
-It was the day before last.

585
00:32:01,294 --> 00:32:02,796
-Was it?
-Yeah.

586
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:06,257
Good morning.

587
00:32:06,341 --> 00:32:08,552
-Morning? Were you sleeping?
-Morning.

588
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:11,930
-Welcome back.
-I was taking a nap.

589
00:32:13,849 --> 00:32:16,435
We sort of...

590
00:32:16,518 --> 00:32:18,437
